<IN>
BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   CALABASAS, Calif. -- Weaver Arms Inc., which is being
reorganized under Chapter 11 federal bankruptcy protection,
said it has entered into an agreement to acquire Video USA, a
New York-based chain of video rental stores.
   Video USA, which consists of 68 stores, is owned by a
group of limited partnerships. Daniel Lezak, president of
Weaver Arms, said the 300 limited partners of Video USA will
receive 20 million units of Weaver, or 60% of the company, in
exchange for Video USA. Mr. Lezak said the units will consist
of common stock and warrants to purchase common stock.
